text:
>Hey Portland! I’m helping produce a small launch party with Scout Notebooks and Business For A Better Portland next Thursday 28th, 4—6pm, at The Redd (the XOXO 2014 venue!)

>Scout is producing a pocket guide to civic engagement in Oregon called “We The People Are Powerful!“, to help with grassroots organizing and understanding Oregon’s legislature and election cycles. It lists local organizations that need your support, and information on how to contact your local representatives.

>You should come pick one up! City Councilwoman Chloe Eudaly will be speaking, along with some of the organizations who are included in the guide.

>You can register here: <https://www.eventbrite.com/e/dwp-2017-guide-launch-we-the-people-are-powerful-tickets-32671720997>

attachments.title: DWP 2017: Guide Launch – We The People Are Powerful!
attachments.text: Scout Books in partnership with Business For A Better Portland present the launch of We The People Are Powerful!, a pocket guide to understanding your rights. It covers grassroots organizing, Oregon's legislature and election cycles, along with contact information for your local representatives. Written by the Scout Books Equity Alliance, and featuring illustrations from Sarah Mirk, Sarah Day, Jillian Barthold and Samantha Cohen.
